de.wagnst.tpe.exercises.exercise2.master

Class Account

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.wagnst.tpe.exercises.exercise2.master.Account

  • public final class Account
extends java.lang.Object
    Account manages bookings of money to a bank account. Every account has an owner as well as a currency. All done transactions to an account (through post()) will get logged in accountHistory. A single item can be gained with the method returnElementInHistory(). A complete bank statement can be printed with the toString() method.

    New instances can be created with the help of the constructor 

         Account account = new Account("Steffen Wagner", Currencies.EURO);

    Objects of this class are immutable. The methods don't change the state of their object, but return a new object.

    Author:
    wagnst
